---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import styles from './self.module.scss';
---

<Layout>
	<div class={styles.pageWrapper}>
		<div class={styles.headerWrapper}>
			<h3>CHAEMIN LEE</h3>
			<img src='stillflower.webp' alt='' />
		</div>
		<div class={styles.gridWrapper}>
			<div class={styles.floatSectionHeader}>
				<h3>†</h3>
			</div>
			<div class={styles.sectionHeader}>
				<h4>Self Description</h4>
			</div>
			<div class={styles.gridItem}>
				<div class={styles.buttonsWrapper}>
					<div class={styles.button}>
						<p><b>Raised in</b> Korea, Japan, and Hawaii</p>
					</div>
					<div class={styles.button}>
						<p><b>Recent Passion:</b> Audio-reactive AI</p>
					</div>
					<div class={styles.button}>
						<p><b>University:</b> Vanderbilt</p>
					</div>
					<div class={styles.button}>
						<p>
							<b>Currently Reading</b>
							<span style='font-style: italic;'>Snow Country</span>
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class={styles.floatSectionHeader}>
				<h3>&lt; Design &gt;</h3>
			</div>
			<div class={styles.floatSectionDescription}>
				<p>
					There are only a few sentences that ever make you really feel
					something deep inside. For me, one of those sentences was a Kanye West
					quote, that "the world can be saved through design". Certain designs
					make you feel things, and I love expressing myself through design.
					This portfolio is one of many ways I do that.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class=`${styles.floatSectionHeader} ${styles.thinSectionHeader}`>
				<h3 style='font-style: oblique;'>&lt; Software &gt;</h3>
			</div>
			<div class={styles.floatSectionDescription}>
				<p>
					Product design in software has changed something fundamental from the
					traditional ways of hardware engineering. We no longer have to wait
					for a prototype to be built before we can see whether our vision
					actually works. You can render an idea in real time, feel it, tear it
					apart, and rebuild it. That immediacy between imagination and
					execution is what pulls me in, along with the sheer imaginative and
					creative power that software has.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class={styles.sectionHeader}>
				<h4>Album Curation</h4>
			</div>
			<div class={styles.gridItem}>
				<div class={styles.albumsBox}>
					<div class={styles.albumWrapper}>
						<img src='ksg.webp' alt='kids see ghosts' />
					</div>
					<div class={styles.albumWrapper}>
						<img src='gybe.webp' alt='lift your skinny fists' />
					</div>
					<div class={styles.albumWrapper}>
						<img src='miles.webp' alt='bitches brew' />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
